    "description": "<p>You conjure a mote of sickly light at a point within range. The mote emits&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">bright light</span>&nbsp;in a 20-foot radius, and&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">dim light</span>&nbsp;for another 20 feet. A non-undead creature that starts its turn in the bright light, or enters the bright light for the first time on a turn, must succeed on a Constitution&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">saving throw</span>&nbsp;or suffer a level of&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">fatigue</span>&nbsp;.</p>\n<p>Additionally, if it suffers this fatigue, all&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">undead</span>&nbsp;in the area of bright light gain 2d8 temporary hit points and those in the area of dim light gain 1d8 temporary hit points. On a successful save, a creature is&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">immune</span>&nbsp;to the effect until it leaves the area.</p>",
